MNUMBER 131
NAME gulivira
*DESCRIPTION_START
The gulivira is a mottled gray color with large lumpy black protrusions on its skin. Bristling spines are set into its body, looking sharp and dangerous. The fish is fairly large, and due to its coloration is hard to spot amongst the rocks.
*DESCRIPTION_END
