NUMBER 2340 
NAME Under the Inner Sea
REGION 12
CHANNEL 777
FIXED_LIGHT
UNDERSEA
EXIT D 2341
*DESCRIPTION_START
Enormous fronds of kelp and seaweed float lazily in the currents,
occasionally catching a glint of sunlight through the water. Schools of
fish dart here and there, scattering around you, then reforming in the
distance. Below you, the water gets murkier, and it is nearly
impossible to see the ocean floor.
*DESCRIPTION_END

;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
NUMBER 2341 
NAME Underwater Caves
REGION 62
CHANNEL 777
FIXED_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
UNDERSEA
EXIT U 2340
EXIT W 2342
*DESCRIPTION_START
Unusual plants grow among the stones scattered across the ocean floor,
some barely inches high, others towering out of sight. Through the murky
water, you sense movement more than see it. Off to the west, the light
seems to swallowed by a dark cave opening.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFENTRY
  ECHO ALL A sea turtle swims slowly by, seeming totaly disinterested.
ENDIF
;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
NUMBER 2342 
NAME Ocean Floor, Caves
REGION 62
CHANNEL 777
FIXED_LIGHT
UNDERSEA
EXIT E 2341
*DESCRIPTION_START
A sandy cliff rises directly in front of you, its walls pockmarked with
crevices and openings. The underwater vegetation seems to grow thicker
to the east than it does here, the plants considerably smaller. A stray
fish or two swims by, eyeing you curiously before darting into a
crevice.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 69 VAL2=2343
IFPREVERB GO 0
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
    ECHO PLAYER You can't seem to find the right crevice.
  ELSE
  DISBAND
  ECHO PLAYER You wriggle into a narrow crevice.
  ECHO OTHERS %n wriggles into a narrow crevice.
  MOVE 2343
ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB SEARCH -1
  clearverb
  RANDOM DUMMY1 1 10 0
  IFVAR DUMMY1 = 1
    ECHO PLAYER You peer into one of the crevices, and realize that it is the entrance to a cave.
    EQUAL FLAG1 1
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY1 = 2
    ECHO PLAYER You search carefully, and find a gold coin!
    NEWITEM -1 1223 ADJ1=147
  endif
  IFVAR DUMMY1 > 2
    ECHO PLAYER You search carefully, and find nothing.
  endif
  ECHO PLAYER [Round: 3 sec]
  EQUAL ROUNDTIME 3
ENDIF
;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
NUMBER 2343 
NAME Sea Cave, Entrance 
REGION 62
CHANNEL 777
FIXED_LIGHT
UNDERSEA
*DESCRIPTION_START
The narrow passage twists and turns through the cliff's interior. In
most places, the walls are barely two feet apart, forcing you to edge
along sideways. A faint light ahead at least tells you that there is an
end to it.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFENTRY
  ECHO PLAYER You squeeze through the narrow entrance, turning sideways and edging along.
  ECHO OTHERS %n squeezes into the narrow entrance turning sideways.
  EQUAL ROUNDTIME 10
  ECHO PLAYER [Round: 15 sec]
  PLREVENT 3
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO PLAYER The walls narrow further, and for a moment you worry that you'll have to turn back...
  ECHO OTHERS %n edges along through the crevice, muttering...
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO PLAYER ...but eventually, you find yourself able to move more easily.
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO PLAYER Finally, the narrow passage opens onto a ledge overlooking a deep cavern.
  ECHO OTHERS %n steps out of the crevice.
  MOVE 2344
  SHOWROOM 2344
  AFFECT 2344
  ECHO OTHERS %n steps out onto the ledge.
ENDIF
;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
NUMBER 2344 
NAME On the Ledge
REGION 62
CHANNEL 777
FIXED_LIGHT
UNDERSEA
EXIT N 2345
EXIT S 2346
EXIT D 2347
*DESCRIPTION_START
A narrow ledge runs along the cliff face, providing barely enough
footing for travel in single file. Far below, you see brief flashes of
light and movement, and off in the distance you can barely make out
another cliff face. The ledge extends north and south, curving out of
sight in either direction.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 69 VAL2=2348
;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
NUMBER 2345 
NAME Sea Cavern, North Ledge
REGION 62
CHANNEL 777
FIXED_LIGHT
UNDERSEA
EXIT S 2344
EXIT D 2349
*DESCRIPTION_START
A narrow ledge runs along the cliff face, providing barely enough
footing for travel in single file. Far below, you see brief flashes of
light and movement, and off in the distance you can barely make out
another cliff face. The ledge curves out of sight to the south,
and completely disappears to the north.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
NUMBER 2346 
NAME Sea Cavern, South Ledge
REGION 62
CHANNEL 777
FIXED_LIGHT
EXIT N 2344
EXIT D 2350
*DESCRIPTION_START
A narrow ledge runs along the cliff face, providing barely enough
footing for travel in single file. Far below, you see brief flashes of
light and movement, and off in the distance you can barely make out
another cliff face. The ledge extends curves out of sight to the north,
and drops off suddenly to the south.
sight in either direction.
*DESCRIPTION_END
